    <h1>Phantom vs Solflare: Best Solana Wallet Compared</h1>
    <div class="meta">Published: May 16, 2026 | Updated: May 19, 2026 | 7 min read | Category: Wallets</div>
    <p>Choosing the right wallet is the most important decision for any Solana user. <strong>Phantom</strong> and <strong>Solflare</strong> are the two most popular Solana wallets, each with millions of users. This comparison breaks down their features, security, staking capabilities, and ecosystem integration to help you decide which is best for your needs.</p>

    <h2>Phantom Wallet Overview</h2>
    <p>Phantom is the most popular Solana wallet with over 5 million monthly active users. It offers a beautiful, intuitive interface that works as both a browser extension and mobile app. Phantom supports Solana, Ethereum, and Polygon - making it a great multi-chain wallet. Key features include built-in token swaps, NFT gallery, dApp browser, and one-click staking.</p>

    <h2>Solflare Wallet Overview</h2>
    <p>Solflare is a Solana-native wallet with deep staking features and Ledger hardware wallet integration. It offers a comprehensive staking dashboard, validator analytics, and multi-account management. Solflare is available as a web wallet, browser extension, and mobile app. It's the preferred wallet for serious stakers and power users.</p>

    <h2>Feature Comparison</h2>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Feature</th><th>Phantom</th><th>Solflare</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Ease of Use</td><td>Excellent</td><td>Good</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Multi-Chain Support</td><td>Solana, Ethereum, Polygon</td><td>Solana only</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Staking Dashboard</td><td>Basic</td><td>Advanced</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Ledger Support</td><td>Yes</td><td>Yes (better)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>NFT Gallery</td><td>Built-in</td><td>Built-in</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Mobile App</td><td>Yes</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
      <tr><td>DEX Integration</td><td>Jupiter integrated</td><td>Jupiter integrated</td></tr>
    </table>

    <h2>Verdict</h2>
    <p>For most users, <strong>Phantom is the better choice</strong> - it's more user-friendly, supports multiple chains, and has excellent dApp integration. For serious stakers and power users who want granular validator control and advanced analytics, <strong>Solflare is the winner</strong>. Many users actually use both wallets for different purposes.</p>

